[2]
Date: Sat, 09 Nov 2002 13:49:06 -0500
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Canoe.com 8 Nov 2002 (edited)
<http://www.canoe.ca/NationalTicker/CANOE-wire.PEI-E-Coli.html>
Administrator of Prince Edward Island hospital says _E. coli_ hasn't spread
---------------------------
CHARLOTTETOWN (CP) -- The administrator of a PEI hospital where
several people are suspected to have contracted a deadly strain of
_E. coli_ says there haven't been further signs of the illness.
Cecil Ballard said that since 29 Oct, 2002, a total of 14 patients
and 31 staff at Hillsborough hospital have experienced symptoms of
_E. coli_ at the hospital. The official said there has been no
further cases since Wednesday, 6 Oct.
2 patients died this week, but so far there is no relation between
those deaths and _E. coli_. 2 staff have been confirmed positive for
_E. coli_. One is in hospital while the other is resting at home.
Officials said the results from cultures taken from the victims will
not be back until sometime Saturday. Meantime, staff who showed
symptoms will not be allowed back to work until all tests come back
negative.
[There is no information linking the two outbreaks in these distant
provinces. - Mod.LM]
